    <note>She Weichang [14237] CBD has death in 1009, but SHY:Fyu has it in 1014, which is also date of succession of younger brother Weizhong [14238]. I use SHY date. SHY:Fyu, 21.3b-4a, 5a, 5a-5b, 5b; SHY:Fyi, 7.8a; YH, 154.30b. CBD, 2, 1077.From Hartwell's ACTIVITY table:997:  Succeded elder brother Weizheng as prefect of Fuzhou because Weizheng mad and not able to govern prf1005:  Fuzhou inhabited by foreigners (fan) and Chinese (Han), who dwell together &amp; difficult to govern.1009:  His petition to come to the capital was approved.1009:  Arrived at capital w/staff of 47 men &amp; presented horses (mingma) &amp; feasts, rewards, etc.1014:  He died &amp; mother Liang's request approved that next son, Weizhong succeed as prefect of Fuzhou.</note>
